## Frequently Asked Questions
* **Is Plaid free for consumers?**: Yes. Consumers can use Plaid to safely connect and control the financial information they share with apps or services at no cost.
* **Can I try Plaid for free?**: Absolutely. Our Limited Production service allows you to make up to 200 API calls with each available product using live data. This is the best way to start learning about and testing Plaid’s APIs.
* **How much does Plaid cost?**: We offer three basic pricing models based on the product(s) you’re using and how it’s designed: one-time, subscription, and per-request.
* **Does Plaid offer discounts?**: We offer volume discounts based on the length of your contract and/or the minimum monthly commitment you choose. For more details, please reach out to our sales team.
* **How does Pay-as-You-Go billing work?**: It’s simple—once you sign up for the products you need in Plaid's production dashboard, we’ll charge the card on file for the connected items (accounts). No upfront commitments. Only pay for what you use.